==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greatness
<hw>Great"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>gre⟦aacute⟧tnes</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state,
condition, or quality of being great; <as>as, <ex>greatness</ex> of
size, <ex>greatness</ex> of mind, power, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pride; haughtiness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is not of pride or <qex>greatness</qex> that he cometh not
aboard your ships.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>great-niece</ent>⟦br⟧
